values: I finally got back from Bodrum. that fucking place was 114.8 degrees every goddamn day, so i spent the days swimming. fun times but im counting down the hours till I return home.

so;
Here I am sitting in my cousin's apartment, enjoying some bread and excessively salty cheeze, chilling in my new exotic designer jeans, waiting for his coworke'rs niece to pick me up for more shopping and sightseeing.  Today I attempted to do some laundry: what a mistake. to begin with, it took me 45 minutes and two dictionaries to figure out that I'm supposed to set the damn machine to "Sensitive" and then hope it wont fuck up my brights with hot water. What else... aone I've successfully bought bread, crossed the Marmara sea twice on ferries, and  taken a dolmush down to Taksim square. Looks like i'm getting a little better at being turkish. and I've only got three weeks left here...

ahhh i love that song more than...... more than pie!!!!!!! and i loove pie!!!! the 4th was sweeet, some friends and i went paintballing out in mission viejo in the middle of the night, so sweet. I of course had the badass gun with not one, but two types of laser sights and an enormous 200 round hopper yessss... now i need to get caught back up on work! yikes! too much play not enough work, also i havent been around a computer for a long time so i havent updated this journal for dayyyyys... hmm what happened in the time that has passed? i dont know... you cant look back you can never look back ;) i think i've just been working nonstop and being busy with stupid crap, like listening to my dad insisting that there is no way I can change my brake rotors and pads and i'll HAVE to take it to a "professional mechanic" to get that done. i want to see the look on his face when he sees my new performance rotors and pads hehehe. they told me that i was snoring last night! and that they could hear it from the street! ak, i let them know about the monster who follows me when i sleep and growls and stuff while i'm asleep... they think its snoring... *sigh* feels like life is boring again. theres nothing driving me... i want a dog.

So yes after saturday i'll be fully trained in selling housewares, cutlery and sporting knives... and more importantly, i'll be making money :D. 

F-cking curbs. one snuck up on me last night, my left steering/suspension is f-cked. totally f-cked. i bent my front drivers side rim... badly. f-cking curbs. so now i get to ride my motorcycle to work yay! :/ yeah i'll be the guy riding through long beach wearing a suit and tie and a helmet.

so now i'm just yeah... going to play moto GP or something until she gets here because my parents are being retarted and not going shopping with me. I need more formalwear. alot more formalwear... dress to impress for success, beotch!

yeah umm.. the concert was FUCKING AWESOME!!!!!!! oh oh oh, there were like 10 people at the whole concert wearing straw hats, and during the Foo Fighter's set one of the hats got up on the stage. Dave Grohl picked it up and was like "Whoever wore this hat here is a loser!!" and of course that made us laugh hysterically... yeah all of steve's directions were wrong. he gave us the wrong directions to the airport, then when we got there, he gave us the wrong directions to the hotel, then he told us it would take about 2 hours to get to the concert grounds with traffic. it took 15 minutes so we got there hella early, but we convinced the security that we were with the foo fighters so we hung out in the back in the shade with all the security peeps. yeah the show kicked ass, other than the near-panic attack i had when Davey's voice gave out on him during Totalimmortal (sooo funny...) and i thought that they may end the set early. nope didnt happen, Davey is a tough mother f-cker!!! even in vinyl pants... and YES they played This Time Imperfect!!! like for the first time ever live!!! *kicks so much a$$* it was a fine moment. Then Foo Fighters just rocked everything, and at the end Dave Grohl gave props to Havok, and all was well. 

the weekend was bueno on the whole... the 114 degree weather on sunday didnt exactly feel good, but all the bands kinda made up for that. and all the flashing. [hillbilly voice] yup they do things a little differntly in Tucson [/hillbilly voice] lotta titty bein flashed. it was interestin, i swear some of those girls were like 14 and other ones were like 40. there were some not-so-pretty sights. Dave Grohl even started making fun of em :D *he is SO the man!!!* 

but umm yeah i've decided that i dislike Hicks even more than i dislike Hippies. at least hippies are nice to you, hicks gotta drink beer and bump into ya and think that fat chicks can crowd-surf...

hotel room was kick ass though... yes... kick ass. 

now on to the important stuff: Band practice tomorrow with the best band ever!!!! Scott Yanc and his Popular Friends!!! *winks at adam and kellie* okay okay we'll consider another name....

well kids, thats it for now, i've got a dentist appointment bright and early tomorrow.... late!

geez, its been how long since i updated this sheeit? oh wait, i havent been home since.... well yesterday but that doesnt count. I was just home for all of an hour (or maybe less) to clean my room really quick and get going again, and still as always, show up sorta late to shane's show. Twas still a good show, good energy n' sound mixin n' stuff. sorta motivates me to *thinking* oh thats right, maybe have a complete song! our song kicks soooo much ass, the hardcore song... yes i MUST remember the chorus we came up with D, *thinking* umm... 8? 10? whatever i'll figure it out... yeah im at kellies right now *shout out yo! kellie!* because.... i feel like i've neglected this journal. I spent the night out at friends' houses since....i think wednesday. yeah wednesday. *yess* its time to go home tonight.... hopefully... anyways our song is so damn catchy! i cant get it out of my head... ohhhhh almost completely forgot, I'm now a vandal. guilty of breaking *snicker* and entering. yeah... and stealing from old dead people. last night was cool, but scary as f-ck at the same time, we broke into some old abandoned ghost house in seal and freeek looted and pillaged the place looking for money. hilarious, he found like $5 in change and went nuts "look guys! money! weeeee!!!!" *shakes head* and then i used my awesome skills of destroying stuff to break locked doors and get us a pad so yes, bed at 6am, getup call at 10am *smacks head on desk* i'm soooooooo tired! and i'm kinda shocked, i got a sunburn today... bad. I cant belive it, i never burn!!!!!! i tan!!!! well not today, Jeff and I rode bicycles to the beach (yes a long f-cking way!!!) and now my legs are dead, i weigh a little bit less, i'm burnt... but i'm looking much better ;). time to go learn how to make food... hmm *knows its going to be complicated* :/

hmm....dum de dum de dum... time for a little midnight snack... and before i forget, this is a reminder that we have to write out the script for "It came from below and its pissed off!" hehehehe *giggles furiously* 'boop boop' captain! its really pissed off! *rolls on floor laughing* geez im such a goofy kid....

wow its good to finally be home after... not being home since saturday. well its looking like life is just one big party after another, saturday was Jay's barbeque, yessss a bunch o' rowdy bikers, then sunday was matt's barbeque and that was fun, jen's cute friend was there again and... yeah... she's cute. and the signs are looking good...*closes in for the kill*

anyways i finally had the R1 out this weekend and rode it damn near everywhere, and the driveway is finally cleared up a little. the front of our house is lookin gooood i gotta hand it to the mexicans, they can do a kickass job.

well... band practice didnt go so well... kinda because it didnt really happen today, hope adam feels better real soon, strep throat is not a pretty illness... and... yeah.

all in all, a productive weekend, had Mucho Mucho fun.... and i dont think i've ever laughed so hard in one weekend ever... so many jokes, "aye aye captain!" and the 'coinstar' story at 10pm hehehe *snickers*

and watching session 9 at like midnight last night...*whew* love watching scary movies with girls... and now registering for classes! oh wait... cant until the 29th...damn.

hell yes! we have a hardcore song! well.... a hardcore riff... but it will be a song soon!!! yesss!!! i finally woke up today and did all the registration crap for cypress college...yay. more school. fun... but on the bright side... band practice again tonight! now we need to work on a name for the band... hrmm...

geez finally.... stupid cookies not letting me log in to make entries....

anyways the crazy neighbors came over last night and rang the doorbell. I answer the door and mike is standing there holding a corona "get a shirt on and come outside!" hehe so yeah i guess they're getting me a fake ID made so i can go to vegas with them.... oh man... and we're working on getting my gym membership.. if only i had more money...

and these damn mexican workers!!!! 7 IN THE FUCKING MORNING WITH THIER GODDAMN MEXICAN RADIO RIGHT OUTSIDE MY WINDOW. i'm gonna kill my parents for having them do this work to the front of our house. and my dumbass mom "yeah yeah keep your motorcycles in the garage" and this morning i open the garage and what do i see? FUCKING BRICKS, ROCKS AND DIRT TOTALLY BLOCKING THE WHOLE GODDAMN DRIVEWAY.... <BIG> TILL NEXT FUCKING WEEK THEY SAY!!!!! </BIG> F-CK THAT SHIT I"M PISSED OFF.... i'm going to take my bike through the house if i need to, but i cant go that long without riding. poison fucking death.

oh wow oh wow oh wow *all excited* okay adam, kellie, we're going on a road trip to texas to see Kate!!!!! yes the girl from texas! woooooo!!! and i cannot wait for our band practice! what day is it going to be? and .....my sandwich is almost ready...mmmm... food...

two very important things happened last night.
#1. i saw (and touched) a boss hoss motorcycle. a chevy 350 V-8 in a crusier. holy sh-t. the rear tire looked like one of my camaro tires.
#2. Beat Halo on legendary. holy sh-t. i am a legend, i've never even heard of anyone doing this...


okay so Kate has a friend that looks like Rachel Leigh Cook.... this cannot be. if she really does.... i cannot be held responsible for my actions in tex. hahaha she even types her accent! "yall" :D

well today was pretty productive... not!
visited jeff and found out that my chatterbox works with pretty much any 2 way radio! rockin! so we had a fun little cruise down to the beach for lunch, then actually i did do somethign productive, i registered to....register for classes for summer at cypress cc, and yeah. finally finally finally fixed the trunk on my bike, now theres no way that sheeit is poppin open without using the key ;)

hmmm i cant find my windscreen logo anywhere... jay is gonna kill me!!

but on the bright side, i have my old biker buddys to roll with, no more solo crap yessss....

goddamn its so hot in corona! i'm sitting here naked and the window is open, and dammit i'm still cookin!!!
